(13, NULL, 2, 'Classification of custom furniture panels', 'Which kind more fit to you?', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'images/blog/classification-of-custom-furniture-panels-1690094752.jpg', 'Classification of custom furniture panels', 'Panel', '<p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Custom furniture is a trend in modern home decoration, as it can bring unique style and personalized design to the home.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">In custom furniture, panel is a commonly used material because it has a variety of different properties and uses.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">This article will discuss the types of panels commonly used in custom furniture and their characteristics.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">1. Solid wood</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Solid wood is a very popular material for custom furniture. It is made from a single piece of wood, so it has natural and beautiful texture and feel. Solid wood is typically used to make furniture such as tables, chairs, cabinets, beds, and wardrobes. The color and texture of solid wood vary depending on the type of tree, so you can choose different types of solid wood according to your needs and style.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://hongdatfurniture.com/admin/images/content/1690094290.jpg\" data-filename=\"filename\" style=\"width: 717px;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">2. Plywood</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Plywood is a panel made by gluing thin wood sheets together in a specific way. It is typically stronger and more durable than solid wood, so it can be used to make furniture that requires more support. Plywood also comes in many different types, such as multi-layer plywood and single-layer plywood, each with its own characteristics and uses.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://hongdatfurniture.com/admin/images/content/1690094308.jpg\" data-filename=\"filename\" style=\"width: 717px;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">3. Medium-density fiberboard (MDF)</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">MDF is a panel made by gluing wood fibers and resin together. Its density is higher than plywood, so it is stronger and more durable. MDF is typically used to make furniture that requires more support and stability, such as bookshelves, wardrobes, and kitchen cabinets. MDF has a smooth surface that is easy to process and paint, so it can also be used to make various different furniture styles.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://hongdatfurniture.com/admin/images/content/1690094326.jpg\" data-filename=\"filename\" style=\"width: 717px;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">4. Particleboard</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Particleboard is a panel made by gluing wood chips and resin together. It is relatively light in weight, so it is suitable for making lighter furniture, such as desks, wardrobes, and drawers. Particleboard is relatively inexpensive to produce, so it is an ideal choice for many households.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">In general, there are many different types of panels used in custom furniture, each with its own unique characteristics and uses. The choice of the right panel depends on the design, purpose, and budget of the furniture. When choosing a panel, you should consider its material, density, and quality to ensure the stability and appearance of the furniture. In addition, consumers should choose a reliable custom furniture manufacturer to ensure the quality and service of the furniture.</p><p style=\"margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 24px; white-space-collapse: preserve; word-break: break-word; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img src=\"https://hongdatfurniture.com/admin/images/content/1690094349.jpg\" data-filename=\"filename\" style=\"width: 717px;\"><br></p>', 'classification-of-custom-furniture-panels', 'Jul 23', 1, 1, 1, '2023-07-23 02:45:52', '2023-07-23 02:45:52'),
(14, NULL, 2, 'We expanded business scope to house maintanence.', 'Please check work details in the content', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'images/blog/we-expanded-business-scope-to-house-maintanence.-1690263190.png', NULL, NULL, '<ul style=\"margin: 4px 0px; padding-inline-start: 36px; color: rgb(31, 31, 31); font-family: &quot;Google Sans&quot;, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Exterior maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning the exterior, repairing cracks, and painting.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Roof maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning the roof, repairing shingles, and replacing gutters.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Window maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning the windows, replacing seals, and repairing glass.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Door and window maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning doors and windows, replacing seals, and repairing glass.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Interior decoration maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning floors, walls, ceilings, curtains, and repairing damaged walls, floors, and ceilings.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Plumbing and electrical maintenance:&nbsp;This includes inspecting pipes and wires, and replacing damaged pipes and wires.</li><li style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Furniture maintenance:&nbsp;This includes cleaning furniture and repairing damaged furniture.</li></ul>', 'we-expanded-business-scope-to-house-maintanence.', 'Jul 25', 1, 1, 1, '2023-07-25 01:33:10', '2023-07-25 01:33:10');
